          {
            "text": "Katy, Texas, has several reputable options for Platelet-Rich Plasma (PRP) hair loss treatments, ranging from board-certified dermatologists to specialized medical spas. \n\nBelow are the top-rated locations in the Katy area offering PRP for hair restoration:\n\n### **1. Dermatologists & Medical Specialists**\nThese clinics are often preferred by patients seeking a clinical diagnosis alongside their treatment.\n*   **Village Dermatology / Reena Jogi, MD:** Dr. Jogi is a highly recognized specialist in hair loss. She provides comprehensive evaluations and uses PRP in combination with other medical treatments like oral minoxidil or AlmaTED.\n    *   **Location:** 21800 Katy Fwy, Ste 200, Katy, TX 77449\n    *   **Phone:** (713) 487-4061\n*   **Advanced Dermatology:** They offer a specialized \"Pure PRP Plus\" treatment which uses a higher concentration of growth factors. \n    *   **Location:** 23050 Westheimer Pkwy, Katy, TX 77494\n    *   **Phone:** (281) 395-3700\n*   **Integrative Primary Care (Dr. Syed Farhat Zaidi):** This clinic focuses on regenerative medicine and offers PRP therapy to boost blood supply to aging hair follicles.\n    *   **Location:** 21020 Highland Knolls Dr, Katy, TX 77450\n    *   **Phone:** (832) 500-7585\n*   **Parikh Plastic Surgery (Dr. Janak Parikh):** A board-certified plastic surgeon offering PRP combined with **Exosomes** for enhanced regenerative results.\n    *   **Phone:** (713) 467-0146\n\n### **2. Medical Spas & Aesthetic Centers**\nThese facilities often combine PRP with other scalp-rejuvenation technologies.\n*   **4Ever Young Anti-aging Clinic and Medical Spa:** They offer a unique protocol that combines PRP therapy with **HydraFacial Keravive**, which cleanses and exfoliates the scalp to prepare it for the injections.\n    *   **Location:** 25222 Northwest Fwy, Ste 100, Cypress/Katy area\n*   **Luminous MediSpa:** Known for personalized care, they provide traditional PRP injections tailored to the patient's specific hair loss pattern.\n    *   **Location:** 2004 Mason Rd, Katy, TX 77450\n*   **Soo Med Spa:** Provides non-surgical hair restoration using PRP to \"awaken\" dormant follicles, typically serving the Katy and Sugar Land areas.\n    *   **Location:** 23501 Cinco Ranch Blvd, Katy, TX 77494\n*   **Luxe Medical Aesthetics:** Offers PRP as a \"gold standard\" for natural hair restoration without synthetic additives.\n    *   **Location:** 1535 S Mason Rd, Katy, TX 77450\n\n### **What to Expect**\n*   **The Procedure:** A small amount of your blood is drawn and spun in a centrifuge to isolate the platelets. This concentrated plasma is then injected into the thinning areas of your scalp.\n*   **Timeline:** Most clinics recommend an initial series of **3 to 4 treatments** spaced 4 to 6 weeks apart. \n*   **Results:** Reduced shedding is often noticed within weeks, but visible regrowth typically takes **3 to 6 months**.\n*   **Cost:** In the Katy area, PRP sessions generally range from **$600 to $1,500 per session**, depending on whether it is bundled with other treatments like Microneedling or Exosomes.\n\n**Tip:** Since hair loss can be caused by various factors (genetics, hormones, or nutrition), it is highly recommended to book a consultation with a board-certified dermatologist like those at **Village Dermatology** or **Advanced Dermatology** first to ensure PRP is the right solution for your specific type of hair loss.",
            "thoughtSignature": ""
          }
        ],
